title: @OspreySwim Drops Final Home Meet Against FGCU
text: Amy Taylor .Taylor, the reigning CCSA Swimmer of the Week, played first in the 200 freestyle with a season best time of 1:54.15. The time is the fastest of any Osprey this season. She also placed second in the 500 freestyle (5:08.97) and third in the 200 butterfly (2:12.30).In her final home meet as an Osprey, Kennedy finished fourth in the 100 freestyle with a time of 55.43, just off her season best time of 55.32 last week against Campbell and NCA&T.Kennedy and Taylor teamed up sophomore
